f each potato, then sit them flat in the prepared tin in one even layer. Scatter over the thyme and onions, then pour over the chicken stock.\nSit the pork on top of the potatoes, skin-side up and roast for 30 mins. Reduce the oven to 180C/160C fan/gas 4 for 1 hr 30 mins, until the skin is crisp. Transfer the pork to a board, then cover loosely with foil and leave to rest for 20 mins.\nReturn the tin with the potatoes to the oven and increase the oven temperature to 200C/180C fan/gas 6 for 25-30 mins until crisp. Carve the pork into generous squares (you can use a bread knife to do this more easily) and serve alongside the fondant potatoes and caramelised pickled onions.", "act_image": "https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/30/2020/08/roast-pork-belly-fondant-potatoes-pickled-onions-b7ef440.jpg", "act_nutrients": {"calories": "609 calories", "fatContent": "42 grams fat", "saturatedFatContent": "15 grams saturated fat", "carbohydrateContent": "15 grams carbohydrates", "sugarContent": "1 grams sugar", "fiberContent": "2 grams fiber", "proteinContent": "42 grams protein", "sodiumContent": "2.3 milligram of sodium"}}